‚öñÔ∏è Python Body Mass Index (BMI) Calculator CLI
A straightforward command-line application built in Python that calculates a user's Body Mass Index (BMI) based on their height and weight, and then classifies the result according to standard health categories.

‚ú® Features
Simple Input: Prompts the user for height in meters (m) and weight in kilograms (kg).

Accurate Calculation: Uses the standard BMI formula: BMI= [WEIGHT/(HEIGHT*HEIGHT)]

Health Classification: Categorizes the calculated BMI into clear health ranges.

Command-Line Interface (CLI): Easy to run directly from any terminal.

üõ†Ô∏è Prerequisites
This application requires only Python 3.x and no external libraries.

Python 3.x must be installed on your system.

üöÄ Installation and Setup
1. Clone the Repository
You can clone this project to your local machine using git:

git clone [https://github.com/your-username/python-bmi-calculator.git](https://github.com/your-username/python-bmi-calculator.git)
cd python-bmi-calculator

2. Run the Application
Since there are no external dependencies, you can run the application directly:

python bmi_calculator.py

üí° Usage Example
The script will prompt you sequentially for your height and weight, and then immediately display the result.

$ python bmi_calculator.py

===================================
  BODY MASS INDEX (BMI) CALCULATOR
===================================

Enter your height in meters (m): 1.75
Enter your weight in kilograms (kg): 70

--- RESULTS ---
Your Calculated BMI: 22.86
Classification: Normal Weight

Stay healthy!
